## File Locations

```
d:\xammp\htdocs\cafe\
├── php version\
│   ├── admin.php          (HR Admin Portal)
│   └── index.php          (Employee/Careers Portal)
├── db.php                 (Database connection - can be configured)
├── api.php                (API endpoints - can be built out)
└── admin_api.php          (Admin API endpoints - can be built out)
```

## Database Setup (Optional - For Production)

To connect to real database, edit files and add connection:

```php
$host = 'localhost';
$user = 'root';
$password = '';
$database = 'cafe_hr';

$conn = new mysqli($host, $user, $password, $database);
```

Create database in phpMyAdmin:
1. Open `http://localhost/phpmyadmin`
2. Click "New Database"
3. Name: `cafe_hr`
4. Create tables (users, jobs, applications, onboarding)

or just upload/copy paste the sql

